          </section>
        </score>
      </mdiv>
    </body>
  </music>
</mei>
<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Opening (pickup, mm. 1-4): Straightforward D/A/Bm/G block chords, 2-note RH, 4-note LH.
  Establishes D major clearly. Bm in m.1 voiced as root-pos (B2 F#3 B3 D4).
- Phrase 2 (mm. 5-8): D Δ7 for richness (m.5); ascending RH arpeggio in m.6 (A4→E5→A5)
  provides rhythmic energy in 3/4. High D5 melody in mm.7-8 with RH at F#5 A5.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 9-12): Bm "333" 7th (m.9) is the emotional center. G quartal "44"
  (m.11) provides open color mid-phrase. E7 (non-diatonic) substituted with Bm/D tones.
- Phrase 4 (mm. 13-16): Mostly A and D in alternation. Sus2 voicing in m.14 RH (A4 B4 E5)
  adds interest before final D. G→A in m.15 provides strong IV→V motion to final D.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m.6: RH ascending arpeggio A4→E5→A5 mirrors melody's A→B→C# ascent — parallel 8vb.
- m.10: RH high register A5 drops to F#4 in two steps over dominant A chord.
- m.12: LH bass steps D2→E2 (D→Em), largest bass step in arrangement; smooth otherwise.
- m.15: Chromatic approach C#5 in RH (A chord) leads back to D in m.16.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opening (mm. 1-4): Light 2-note RH, half-note LH block chords. Steady 3/4 hymn feel.
- Phrase 2 (mm. 5-8): D Δ7 and ascending RH arpeggiation build energy. High register.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 9-12): Bm 7th and G quartal create emotional depth. Sustained LH.
- Phrase 4 (mm. 13-16): Sus2 and strong IV→V motion drives to final resolution on D.
-->
